# English in code and routes

**Code, code comments, and URL routes are always English.** User-facing text belongs in i18n locale files (`src/i18n/*.json`), not in paths or identifiers.

## Routes and files

- Page routes and filenames use English slugs: `/presentation/`, `src/pages/presentation.astro`.
- Locale prefixes stay as configured (`/ca/`, `/en/`, `/de/`); the path segment after the prefix is still English.
- Do not use Spanish or Catalan in URL segments, Astro page names, or `localeHref(..., '/.../')` paths.

```text
// BAD
/presentacion/          src/pages/presentacion.astro
localeHref(locale, '/presentacion/')

// GOOD
/presentation/          src/pages/presentation.astro
localeHref(locale, '/presentation/')
```

## Code and comments

- Variables, functions, components, types, CSS classes, and commit scopes: English.
- Inline comments and JSDoc in source: English.
- Agent/task docs and commit messages: English (see `direct-user-prompts.mdc`).

## i18n (localized copy)

- Headings, labels, body copy, meta titles: `src/i18n/es.json`, `ca.json`, `en.json`, `de.json`.
- Navbar **labels** are localized; navbar **href paths** are not.

## Examples

| Layer | English | Localized (i18n only) |
|-------|---------|------------------------|
| Route | `/presentation/` | n/a |
| Nav label key | `nav.presentation` | ES: "Presentación", EN: "Presentation" |
| Page title | `messages.presentation.metaTitle` | per locale JSON |
